{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778987310407,"sessionID":"ses_1cc182dcdffenYJ8A8vrLv0HjW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_txbFKoWmuSGs9BXVGSHJ88Ys","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/CONTRIBUTING.md","offset":1,"limit":250},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/CONTRIBUTING.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ## Guidelines for creating GitHub tickets with contributions to the ontology:\n2: \n3: 1. **Before you submit a new term request, please check to see if the term already exists:** Before submitting suggestions for new ontology terms, check whether the term already exists, either as a primary term or a synonym. To do this, search the ontology using the [AmiGO](http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo) browser. If you feel a synonym is missing, or the textual definition of a term needs clarification, please submit a ticket for that. \n4: \n5: 2. **For new term requests:** Please always provide suggestions for a name, definition, position in hierarchy, references (e.g. PMIDs), associated dbxrefs (e.g., GOC:dph, GOC:aruk), and synonyms, if applicable.  The ontology editors can more easily process term requests when all of this information is provided.  For an example, please see the entry for [recycling endosome](http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/term/GO:0055037). Provide cross references to external databases such as Rhea, EC, KEGG, MetaCyc and TCBD. \n6: \n7: 3. **For updates to relationships:** Provide details of the current relationships, why you think they are wrong or insufficient, and exactly what should be added or removed.\n8: \n9: 4. **If appropriate, please add a label to your ticket:** The labels menu is to the right of the editing boxes when adding a new issue in github. \n10: \n11: ## Other helpful reminders:\n12: \n13: 1. **Write a detailed request:** Please be specific in your request and include as many details as necessary, providing background information, and if possible, suggesting a solution. GOC editors will be better equipped to address your suggestions if you offer details regarding *'what is wrong'*, *'why'*, and *'how to fix it'*.\n14: \n15: 2. **Provide examples and references:** Please always include references (e.g. PMIDs) for new term requests and, for other term-related requests, include also screenshots, or URLs illustrating the current ontology structure. This will be very helpful to GOC ontology editors, as everyone's settings may be different for their GO browser/editor.\n16: \n17: 3. Tickets with insufficient detail will be marked with a *'More info needed'* label to alert the submitter.\n18: \n19: ### On behalf of the GO editorial team, many thanks!\n20:    \n\n(End of file - total 20 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## Guidelines for creating GitHub tickets with contributions to the ontology:\n\n1. **Before you submit a new term request, please check to see if the term already exists:** Before submitting suggestions for new ontology terms, check whether the term already exists, either as a primary term or a synonym. To do this, search the ontology using the [AmiGO](http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo) browser. If you feel a synonym is missing, or the textual definition of a term needs clarification, please submit a ticket for that. \n\n2. **For new term requests:** Please always provide suggestions for a name, definition, position in hierarchy, references (e.g. PMIDs), associated dbxrefs (e.g., GOC:dph, GOC:aruk), and synonyms, if applicable.  The ontology editors can more easily process term requests when all of this information is provided.  For an example, please see the entry for [recycling endosome](http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/term/GO:0055037). Provide cross references to external databases such as Rhea, EC, KEGG, MetaCyc and TCBD. \n\n3. **For updates to relationships:** Provide details of the current relationships, why you think they are wrong or insufficient, and exactly what should be added or removed.\n\n4. **If appropriate, please add a label to your ticket:** The labels menu is to the right of the editing boxes when adding a new issue in github. \n\n## Other helpful reminders:\n\n1. **Write a detailed request:** Please be specific in your request and include as many details as necessary, providing background information, and if possible, suggesting a solution. GOC editors will be better equipped to address your suggestions if you offer details regarding *'what is wrong'*, *'why'*, and *'how to fix it'*.\n\n2. **Provide examples and references:** Please always include references (e.g. PMIDs) for new term requests and, for other term-related requests, include also screenshots, or URLs illustrating the current ontology structure. This will be very helpful to GOC ontology editors, as everyone's settings may be different for their GO browser/editor.\n\n3. Tickets with insufficient detail will be marked with a *'More info needed'* label to alert the submitter.\n\n### On behalf of the GO editorial team, many thanks!\n   ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"CONTRIBUTING.md","time":{"start":1778987310350,"end":1778987310404}},"id":"prt_e33e81d06001jn0XiYPZ6wMHVV","sessionID":"ses_1cc182dcdffenYJ8A8vrLv0HjW","messageID":"msg_e33e80705001uiCDcDIMRJ0XHz"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778987310552,"sessionID":"ses_1cc182dcdffenYJ8A8vrLv0HjW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_yyBLvqLOfDTEUl6O6TAOM3kl","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"obo-grep.pl --noheader -r 'id: GO:(0097711|1905353|1905349)' src/ontology/go-edit.obo","timeout":120000,"workdir":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go","description":"Shows target term stanzas"},"output":"[Term]\nid: GO:0097711\nname: ciliary basal body-plasma membrane docking\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The docking of a cytosolic centriole/basal body to the plasma membrane via the ciliary transition fibers. In some species this may happen via an intermediate step, by first docking to the ciliary vesicle via the ciliary transition fibers. The basal body-ciliary vesicle then relocates to the plasma membrane, followed by the ciliary vesicle fusing with the plasma membrane, effectively attaching the basal body to the plasma membrane.\" [GOC:cilia, PMID:13978319, PMID:23348840, PMID:23530209, PMID:25686250, PMID:26981235]\ncomment: Basal bodies in jawed vertebrates appear to first attach to a ciliary vesicle. It is unclear how specific this is to jawed vertebrates or if other organisms also employ this sequence. Some species like Giardia intestinalis do not relocate their basal bodies to the plasma membrane, but have their axonemes extend through the cytosol to then protrude out of the cell to form flagella.\nsynonym: \"anchoring of the basal body to the plasma membrane\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"ciliary basal body docking\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0140056 ! organelle localization by membrane tethering\nrelationship: part_of GO:0060271 ! cilium assembly\ncreated_by: pr\ncreation_date: 2016-08-05T16:12:33Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:1905349\nname: ciliary transition zone assembly\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a ciliary transition zone.\" [GO_REF:0000079, GOC:cilia, GOC: