{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778987796347,"sessionID":"ses_1cc182dcdffenYJ8A8vrLv0HjW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_tqK00aJNV8XbQy6SD7KqBNwO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_0060271.obo","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_0060271.obo</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: [Term]\n2: id: GO:0060271\n3: name: cilium assembly\n4: namespace: biological_process\n5: alt_id: GO:0042384\n6: def: \"The assembly of a cilium, a specialized eukaryotic organelle that consists of a filiform extrusion of the cell surface. Each cilium is bounded by an extrusion of the cytoplasmic membrane, and contains a regular longitudinal array of microtubules, anchored basally in a centriole.\" [GOC:BHF, GOC:cilia, GOC:dph, GOC:kmv, GOC:pr, GOC:vw, ISBN:0198506732, PMID:13978319, PMID:27350441]\n7: comment: Note that we deem cilium and microtubule-based flagellum to be equivalent.\n8: synonym: \"ciliogenesis\" EXACT []\n9: synonym: \"cilium biogenesis\" RELATED [GOC:mah]\n10: synonym: \"cilium formation\" EXACT []\n11: synonym: \"cilium morphogenesis\" RELATED []\n12: synonym: \"cilium organization\" RELATED [GOC:dph]\n13: synonym: \"microtubule-based flagellum assembly\" EXACT []\n14: intersection_of: GO:0022607 ! cellular component assembly\n15: intersection_of: results_in_assembly_of GO:0005929 ! cilium\n16: relationship: has_part GO:0035082 ! axoneme assembly\n17: relationship: has_part GO:0035735 ! intraciliary transport involved in cilium assembly\n18: relationship: has_part GO:0061512 ! protein localization to cilium\n19: relationship: has_part GO:0097712 ! trans-Golgi to periciliary membrane compartment transport\n20: relationship: has_part GO:1905349 ! ciliary transition zone assembly\n21: relationship: starts_with GO:0097711 ! ciliary basal body-plasma membrane docking\n22: \n\n(End of file - total 22 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"[Term]\nid: GO:0060271\nname: cilium assembly\nnamespace: biological_process\nalt_id: GO:0042384\ndef: \"The assembly of a cilium, a specialized eukaryotic organelle that consists of a filiform extrusion of the cell surface. Each cilium is bounded by an extrusion of the cytoplasmic membrane, and contains a regular longitudinal array of microtubules, anchored basally in a centriole.\" [GOC:BHF, GOC:cilia, GOC:dph, GOC:kmv, GOC:pr, GOC:vw, ISBN:0198506732, PMID:13978319, PMID:27350441]\ncomment: Note that we deem cilium and microtubule-based flagellum to be equivalent.\nsynonym: \"ciliogenesis\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"cilium biogenesis\" RELATED [GOC:mah]\nsynonym: \"cilium formation\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"cilium morphogenesis\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"cilium organization\" RELATED [GOC:dph]\nsynonym: \"microtubule-based flagellum assembly\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: GO:0022607 ! cellular component assembly\nintersection_of: results_in_assembly_of GO:0005929 ! cilium\nrelationship: has_part GO:0035082 ! axoneme assembly\nrelationship: has_part GO:0035735 ! intraciliary transport involved in cilium assembly\nrelationship: has_part GO:0061512 ! protein localization to cilium\nrelationship: has_part GO:0097712 ! trans-Golgi to periciliary membrane compartment transport\nrelationship: has_part GO:1905349 ! ciliary transition zone assembly","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"terms/GO_0060271.obo","time":{"start":1778987796337,"end":1778987796345}},"id":"prt_e33ef8766001KwulhBd4lCO9tZ","sessionID":"ses_1cc182dcdffenYJ8A8vrLv0HjW","messageID":"msg_e33ef70820016K7x31Df2oAxxN"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778987796416,"sessionID":"ses_1cc182dcdffenYJ8A8vrLv0HjW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_seeHFOicw6rnjIC8hWa9cSXZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_0097711.obo","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_0097711.obo</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: [Term]\n2: id: GO:0097711\n3: name: ciliary basal body-plasma membrane docking\n4: namespace: biological_process\n5: def: \"The docking of a cytosolic centriole/basal body to the plasma membrane via the ciliary transition fibers. In some species this may happen via an intermediate step, by first docking to the ciliary vesicle via the ciliary transition fibers. The basal body-ciliary vesicle then relocates to the plasma membrane, followed by the ciliary vesicle fusing with the plasma membrane, effectively attaching the basal body to the plasma membrane.\" [GOC:cilia, PMID:13978319, PMID:23348840, PMID:23530209, PMID:25686250, PMID:26981235]\n6: comment: Basal bodies in jawed vertebrates appear to first attach to a ciliary vesicle. It is unclear how specific this is to jawed vertebrates or if other organisms also employ this sequence. Some species like Giardia intestinalis do not relocate their basal bodies to the plasma membrane, but have their axonemes extend through the cytosol to then protrude out of the cell to form flagella.\n7: synonym: \"anchoring of the basal body to the plasma membrane\" RELATED []\n8: synonym: \"ciliary basal body docking\" EXACT []\n9: is_a: GO:0140056 ! organelle localization by membrane tethering\n10: relationship: part_of GO:0060271 ! cilium assembly\n11: created_by: pr\n12: creation_date: 2016-08-05T16:12:33Z\n13: \n\n(End of file - total 13 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"[Term]\nid: GO:0097711\nname: ciliary basal body-plasma membrane docking\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The docking of a cytosolic centriole/basal body to the plasma membrane via the ciliary transition fibers. In some species this may happen via an intermediate step, by first docking to the ciliary vesicle via the ciliary transition fibers. The basal body-ciliary vesicle then relocates to the plasma membrane, followed by the ciliary vesicle fusing with the plasma membrane, effectively attaching the basal body to the plasma membrane.\" [GOC:cilia, PMID:13978319, PMID:23348840, PMID:23530209, PMID:25686250, PMID:26981235]\ncomment: Basal bodies in jawed vertebrates appear to first attach to a ciliary vesicle. It is unclear how specific this is to jawed vertebrates or if other organisms also employ this sequence. Some species like Giardia intestinalis do not relocate their basal bodies to the plasma membrane, but have their axonemes extend through the cytosol to then protrude out of the cell to form flagella.\nsynonym: \"anchoring of the basal body to the plasma membrane\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"ciliary basal body docking\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0140056 ! organelle localization by membrane tethering\nrelationship: part_of GO:0060271 ! cilium assembly\ncreated_by: pr\ncreation_date: 2016-08-05T16:12:33Z\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"terms/GO_0097711.obo","time":{"start":1778987796395,"end":1778987796415}},"id":"prt_e33ef87a7001wpfDG44DVTsJG0","sessionID":"ses_1cc182dcdffenYJ8A8vrLv0HjW","messageID":"msg_e33ef70820016K7x31Df2oAxxN"}}
